# libFuzzer writes mutated inputs into `corpus/<target>/` as it runs,
# naming each file by its SHA-1 (40 lowercase hex chars). Those files
# are local fuzzing state, not source: they vary per machine and per
# run, and replaying them gains us nothing the deterministic seeds in
# `gen/gen_corpus.rs` don't already cover.
#
# Strategy: ignore the 40-hex-char names libFuzzer produces, but keep
# every file with a descriptive name (e.g. `inference_minimal`).
# Anything committed must therefore have a human-chosen name.

# Match a basename of exactly 40 hex characters (libFuzzer's SHA-1).
[0-9a-f][0-9a-f][0-9a-f][0-9a-f][0-9a-f][0-9a-f][0-9a-f][0-9a-f][0-9a-f][0-9a-f][0-9a-f][0-9a-f][0-9a-f][0-9a-f][0-9a-f][0-9a-f][0-9a-f][0-9a-f][0-9a-f][0-9a-f][0-9a-f][0-9a-f][0-9a-f][0-9a-f][0-9a-f][0-9a-f][0-9a-f][0-9a-f][0-9a-f][0-9a-f][0-9a-f][0-9a-f][0-9a-f][0-9a-f][0-9a-f][0-9a-f][0-9a-f][0-9a-f][0-9a-f][0-9a-f]
